ANC TO CONDUCT NATIONWIDE ANTI-RACISM PICKETS The African National Congress (ANC) will tomorrow, Tuesday. 2nd of March 2021 conduct nationwide pickets against the scourge of racism at eNCA offices and other centres . The nationwide pickets at the eNCA offices follows the widely publicized racial conduct of eNCA journalist, Lindsay Dentlinger as well as the subsequent justification of such deplorable conduct by the eNCA management.eval(ez_write_tag([[336,280],'politicsweb_co_za-box-3','ezslot_2',112,'0','0'])); The pickets will take place, in line with Covid-19 regulations, under the following details: Date: 02 March 2021eval(ez_write_tag([[468,60],'politicsweb_co_za-medrectangle-3','ezslot_3',113,'0','0'])); Time:10h00-12h00 Venue: Outside ENCA offices Please note that in provinces where there are no eNCA offices, the pickets will take place at Human Rights Commission offices or nearest police station.  Statement issued by the ANC, 1 March 2021